  "text": "Combined with the rank formulae above, Equation 5 implies that rk( HF (−Σ(B n − ,2 ))) = rk( HF (−Σ(B n,2 ))) + rk( HF (−Σ(B u n − ,2 ))). Therefore, our surgery exact triangle splits into a short exact sequence; in particular, the map G is injective. Now, let us assume that c + (ξ n,2 ) satisfies Condition R. Then, according to Equation 4 , c + (ξ n,2 ) must have absolute Z 2 grading 1 (and, hence, so does c(ξ n,2 )). Since G sends c(ξ n,2 ) to c(ξ n − ,2 ), and maps induced by cobordisms preserve relative Z 2 gradings (and are homogeneous with respect to these gradings) [CITATION_1] , the injectivity of G forces c(ξ n − ,2 ) (and, hence, c + (ξ n − ,2 )) to have absolute Z 2 grading 1 as well. But since c + (ξ n − ,2 ) has absolute Z 2 grading 1, it must satisfy Condition R, by the analogue of Equation 4 for HF + (−Σ(B n − ,2 )).",
